      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DELIGHTFUL PEG NZ (4) made it three from three at this venue since arriving from NZ when she led to score over this distance last time. Draws a little wider but can maintain her perfect record in WA. FAKENIT (5) was first up for five months when just over a metre off Delightful Peg last start and will be fitter for that. Put together a string of wins and placings against the good three-year-olds last season, highlighted by a WA Oaks win and Derby third. Could turn the tables. AARDIEBYTHESEASIDE NZ (9) cops the outside barrier for her return but she is a quality mare who has won four of seven fresh attempts and owns a strong strike rate at this circuit and distance. COPY CAT QUEEN (8) is another with a wide draw first up but she was good in strong company last campaign and has won three of five when fresh.",
